Two opposition politicians have urged leaders to conduct peaceful campaigns and avoid inciting residents.Kiminini MP Chris Wamalwa and Thomas Mwadeghu (Wundanyi) spoke in Bomet.Mwadeghu said, "Ppoliticians should act as peace ambassadors during their campaign rallies because we do not want to witness such incidences that have happened in the past when we are heading to the polls."Meanwhile, Gatundu South MP Moses Kuria has asked the Kalenjin to ignore connotations that Mt Kenya region will not vote for Deputy President William Ruto in 2022.He said just as Ruto agreed to support President Uhuru Kenyatta by marshalling support from the Kalenjin, the Kikuyu will reciprocate the gesture by backing him for President in 2022."You have our (Kikuyu) support and so you should not get worried," Kuria said in Bomet.